## CLI (`neurex` package)

Installs registry metadata into consumer projects. Depends on **`@neurex/registry`** and **`prompts`** only.

### CLI responsibilities

- Read registry items (files, `dependencies`, `utilities`, `styles`, `target`)
- Install npm deps per item metadata (no hardcoded per-component install branches)
- Wire Tailwind v4 + Vite (supported MVP path)
- Idempotent writes; surface conflicts; never silent overwrite

### `neurex init` / `neurex init vite` installs

**Dev dependencies (Tailwind + Vite path):**

```txt
tailwindcss
@tailwindcss/vite
```

**Vite scaffold also adds:**

```txt
react, react-dom
@types/react, @types/react-dom, @types/node
@vitejs/plugin-react, vite, typescript, prettier
```

### Per-component installs (`neurex add`)

Dependencies come from each `packages/registry/src/items/*.ts` `dependencies` array (see UI section). Shared utility **`cn`** and styles **`theme`** / token CSS are patched via installer, not duplicated in every item file.

### CLI best practices

- New install behavior → registry metadata first, then generic CLI handling
- Tailwind entrypoint path comes from `neurex.config.json` → `tailwind.css` (default applied by `ensureTailwindCssImport`)
- Use `pnpm` in docs and examples; respect consumer `packageManager` when detecting projects
- Test changes under `packages/cli/test` (commands + core installer/tailwind)

