## Tailwind CSS v4

Neurex standardizes on **v4 CSS-first** setup (no `tailwind.config.js` required for the default Vite path).

### Required consumer / playground setup

**1. CSS entrypoint** — first line:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
```

CLI `ensureTailwindCssImport` enforces this in `config.tailwind.css`.

**2. Vite plugin** — `vite.config.ts`:

```typescript
import tailwindcss from "@tailwindcss/vite"

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [tailwindcss(), react()],
})
```

**3. Token CSS** — after Tailwind import:

```css
@import "./styles/tokens.css";
@import "./styles/theme.css";
```

(Paths relative to consumer `paths.styles`; playground uses package imports `@neurex/tokens/tokens.css`.)

**4. Monorepo / library scanning** — when components live outside the app tree, use `@source`:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@source "../../../packages/ui/src";
@source "../../../packages/ui/dist";
```

Without `@source`, Tailwind v4 will not see classes in linked packages.

### Tailwind v4 practices

| Do | Don't |
|----|--------|
| Use `@import "tailwindcss"` | Use legacy `@tailwind base/components/utilities` |
| Use `@tailwindcss/vite` on Vite | Assume PostCSS-only v3 setup |
| Use `@source` for external component paths | Duplicate every utility into app CSS |
| Style via utilities + `cva` + CSS variables | Hand-write token CSS in app repos |
| Use `tailwind-merge` in `cn()` | Concatenate conflicting utilities manually |
| Run Prettier with Tailwind plugin on class strings | Rely on random class order in reviews |

- Prefer **CSS variables** (`var(--nx-*)`) for token-driven values in custom CSS
- Overlay stacking and shadow in `*.variants.ts` must use component token CSS vars, not Tailwind z/shadow scale literals
- Keep **playground** as the visual contract check after token or variant changes
- CLI pins **`tailwindcss`** and **`@tailwindcss/vite`** together on init — keep versions aligned (currently 4.3.x)

