## Dependency boundaries (quick reference)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  subgraph infra [Infrastructure]
    pnpm[pnpm]
    turbo[Turbo]
    tsc[TypeScript]
    tsup[tsup]
    vitest[Vitest]
  end
  subgraph tokens [Tokens]
    tok["@neurex/tokens"]
  end
  subgraph ui [UI]
    u["@neurex/ui"]
    base["@base-ui/react"]
    cva[CVA / clsx / merge]
  end
  subgraph reg [Registry]
    r["@neurex/registry"]
  end
  subgraph cli [CLI]
    c[neurex CLI]
  end
  subgraph consumer [Consumer app]
    app[Vite + React + Tailwind v4]
  end
  infra --> tok
  infra --> u
  infra --> r
  infra --> c
  tok --> u
  r --> c
  c --> app
  u -.->|templates copied| app
  tok -.->|CSS installed| app
```

When adding a dependency, ask: **which layer owns it?** If the answer spans two layers, split the concern (metadata in registry, implementation in ui/tokens, wiring in cli).
